{
  "doc_id": "59622",
  "text": "As a consequence of these SRC effects, it has been argued that the compatibility effect is an index of the additional cognitive resources required to suppress the incompatible observed action and enforce one's own intended action [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In other words, the compatibility effect partly indexes control over the spontaneous urge to imitate, such that incompatible actions are suppressed and one's motor intentions are prioritised.",
